		<div class="container mx-auto px-4 py-8 max-w-2xl">
			<header class="mb-8">
				<h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-2">Logo CDN API Documentation</h1>
				<p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 dark:text-gray-300">Complete guide to using the Logo CDN API</p>
			</header>

			<div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-lg shadow-md p-8 space-y-8">
				<!-- Getting Started -->
				<section>
					<h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-white mb-4">Getting Started</h2>
					<p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-4">
						To use the Logo CDN API, you need an API key. Request one by visiting the 
						<a href="/" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Dashboard</a> and entering your email address.
					</p>
					<p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
						You'll receive a magic link via email. Click the link to view your API key and start using the service.
					</p>
				</section>

				<!-- Authentication -->
				<section>
					<h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-white mb-4">Authentication</h2>
					<p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-4">
						All API requests require an API key. You can provide it in one of three ways:
					</p>
					<ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 ml-4">
						<li>Query parameter: <code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-900 px-2 py-1 rounded">?key=your_api_key</code></li>
						<li>Header: <code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-900 px-2 py-1 rounded">X-Api-Key: your_api_key</code></li>
						<li>Bearer token: <code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-900 px-2 py-1 rounded">Authorization: Bearer your_api_key</code></li>
					</ul>
				</section>

				<!-- Endpoints -->
				<section>
					<h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-white mb-4">API Endpoints</h2>

					<!-- Get Logo by Domain -->
					<div class="mb-6 pb-6 border-b border-gray-200">
						<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-white mb-2">Get Logo by Domain</h3>
						<code class="block bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-900 p-3 rounded mb-3 text-sm">
							GET /&#123;domain&#125;?key=your_api_key&format=png&size=256&greyscale=false
						</code>
						<p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-3">Retrieve a logo by domain name.</p>
						
						<h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-2">Parameters:</h4>
						<ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 ml-4 mb-3">
							<li><code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-900 px-1 rounded">domain</code> - Domain name (e.g., "shopify.com")</li>
							<li><code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-900 px-1 rounded">key</code> - Your API key (required)</li>
							<li><code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-900 px-1 rounded">format</code> - Image format: png, svg, or webp (default: <strong>png</strong>)</li>
							<li><code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-900 px-1 rounded">size</code> - Image size in pixels: 64-512 (default: <strong>256</strong>)</li>
							<li><code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-900 px-1 rounded">greyscale</code> - Convert to greyscale: true or false (default: <strong>false</strong>)</li>
						</ul>

						<h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-2 mt-4">Common Logo Sizes:</h4>
						<ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 ml-4 mb-3">
							<li><code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-900 px-1 rounded">64</code> - Favicon, small icons</li>
							<li><code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-900 px-1 rounded">128</code> - Thumbnails, list views</li>
							<li><code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-900 px-1 rounded">256</code> - Standard web display (default)</li>
							<li><code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-900 px-1 rounded">512</code> - High-res displays, retina screens</li>
						</ul>

						<h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-2">Example:</h4>
						<pre class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-900 p-3 rounded text-sm overflow-x-auto"><code>&lt;img src="https://logo.alisait.com/shopify.com?key=your_api_key&format=png&size=256" alt="Shopify logo" /&gt;</code></pre>
					</div>

					<!-- Get Logo by Company Name -->
					<div class="mb-6 pb-6 border-b border-gray-200">
						<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-white mb-2">Get Logo by Company Name</h3>
						<code class="block bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-900 p-3 rounded mb-3 text-sm">
							GET /name/&#123;companyName&#125;?key=your_api_key&format=png&size=256&greyscale=false
						</code>
						<p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-3">Retrieve a logo by company name.</p>
						
						<h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-2">Parameters:</h4>
						<ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 ml-4 mb-3">
							<li><code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-900 px-1 rounded">companyName</code> - Company name (e.g., "shopify")</li>
							<li><code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-900 px-1 rounded">key</code> - Your API key (required)</li>
							<li><code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-900 px-1 rounded">format</code> - Image format: png, svg, or webp (default: <strong>png</strong>)</li>
							<li><code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-900 px-1 rounded">size</code> - Image size in pixels: 64-512 (default: <strong>256</strong>)</li>
							<li><code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-900 px-1 rounded">greyscale</code> - Convert to greyscale: true or false (default: <strong>false</strong>)</li>
						</ul>

						<h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-2 mt-4">Common Logo Sizes:</h4>
						<ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 ml-4 mb-3">
							<li><code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-900 px-1 rounded">64</code> - Favicon, small icons</li>
							<li><code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-900 px-1 rounded">128</code> - Thumbnails, list views</li>
							<li><code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-900 px-1 rounded">256</code> - Standard web display (default)</li>
							<li><code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-900 px-1 rounded">512</code> - High-res displays, retina screens</li>
						</ul>

						<h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-2">Example:</h4>
						<pre class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-900 p-3 rounded text-sm overflow-x-auto"><code>&lt;img src="https://logo.alisait.com/name/shopify?key=your_api_key&format=svg&size=128" alt="Shopify logo" /&gt;</code></pre>
					</div>

					<!-- Get Statistics -->
					<div class="mb-6 pb-6 border-b border-gray-200">
						<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-white mb-2">Get Usage Statistics</h3>
						<code class="block bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-900 p-3 rounded mb-3 text-sm">
							GET /api/stats?key=your_api_key&days=30
						</code>
						<p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-3">Retrieve usage statistics for your API key(s).</p>
						
						<h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-2">Parameters:</h4>
						<ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 ml-4 mb-3">
							<li><code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-900 px-1 rounded">key</code> - Your API key (or use <code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-900 px-1 rounded">token</code> for magic link)</li>
							<li><code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-900 px-1 rounded">days</code> - Number of days to include in daily breakdown (1-365, default: 30)</li>
						</ul>

						<h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-2">Response:</h4>
						<pre class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-900 p-3 rounded text-sm overflow-x-auto"><code>{`{
  "totalRequests": 1234,
  "todayRequests": 50,
  "thisWeekRequests": 300,
  "thisMonthRequests": 800,
  "keys": [...],
  "dailyBreakdown": [...]
}`}</code></pre>
					</div>

					<!-- Request API Key -->
					<div>
						<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-white mb-2">Request API Key</h3>
						<code class="block bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-900 p-3 rounded mb-3 text-sm">
							POST /api/request-key
						</code>
						<p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-3">Request a new API key by email.</p>
						
						<h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-2">Request Body:</h4>
						<pre class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-900 p-3 rounded text-sm overflow-x-auto mb-3"><code>{`{
  "email": "your@email.com"
}`}</code></pre>

						<h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-2">Response:</h4>
						<pre class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-900 p-3 rounded text-sm overflow-x-auto"><code>{`{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Magic link has been sent to your email...",
  "email": "your@email.com"
}`}</code></pre>
					</div>
				</section>

				<!-- Code Examples -->
				<section>
					<h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-white mb-4">Code Examples</h2>

					<!-- JavaScript -->
					<div class="mb-6">
						<h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-2">JavaScript</h3>
						<pre class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-900 p-4 rounded text-sm overflow-x-auto"><code>{`const apiKey = 'your_api_key';
const domain = 'shopify.com';
const logoUrl = \`https://logo.alisait.com/\${domain}?key=\${apiKey}&format=png&size=256\`;

// Use in img tag
const img = document.createElement('img');
img.src = logoUrl;
img.alt = 'Shopify logo';
document.body.appendChild(img);

// Or fetch directly
fetch(logoUrl)
  .then(response => response.blob())
  .then(blob => {
    const url = URL.createObjectURL(blob);
    // Use the logo
  });`}</code></pre>
					</div>

					<!-- Python -->
					<div class="mb-6">
						<h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-2">Python</h3>
						<pre class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-900 p-4 rounded text-sm overflow-x-auto"><code>{`import requests

api_key = 'your_api_key'
domain = 'shopify.com'
logo_url = f'https://logo.alisait.com/{domain}?key={api_key}&format=png&size=256'

# Download logo
response = requests.get(logo_url)
if response.status_code == 200:
    with open('logo.png', 'wb') as f:
        f.write(response.content)`}</code></pre>
					</div>

					<!-- cURL -->
					<div>
						<h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-2">cURL</h3>
						<pre class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-900 p-4 rounded text-sm overflow-x-auto"><code># Get logo by domain
curl "https://logo.alisait.com/shopify.com?key=your_api_key&format=png&size=256" \
  -o logo.png

# Get logo by company name
curl "https://logo.alisait.com/name/shopify?key=your_api_key&format=svg" \
  -o logo.svg

# Get statistics
curl "https://logo.alisait.com/api/stats?key=your_api_key&days=30" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json"</code></pre>
					</div>
				</section>

				<!-- Error Handling -->
				<section>
					<h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-white mb-4">Error Handling</h2>
					<div class="space-y-3">
						<div class="bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-500 p-4">
							<h4 class="font-semibold text-red-800 mb-1">401 Unauthorized</h4>
							<p class="text-red-700 text-sm">Invalid or missing API key</p>
							<pre class="mt-2 text-xs"><code>{`{"error": "Invalid API key"}`}</code></pre>
						</div>
						<div class="bg-yellow-50 border-l-4 border-yellow-500 p-4">
							<h4 class="font-semibold text-yellow-800 mb-1">429 Too Many Requests</h4>
							<p class="text-yellow-700 text-sm">Rate limit exceeded</p>
							<pre class="mt-2 text-xs"><code>{`{"error": "Rate limit exceeded..."}`}</code></pre>
						</div>
						<div class="bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-500 p-4">
							<h4 class="font-semibold text-red-800 mb-1">404 Not Found</h4>
							<p class="text-red-700 text-sm">Logo not found for the given domain/name</p>
							<pre class="mt-2 text-xs"><code>{`{"error": "Failed to fetch logo"}`}</code></pre>
						</div>
					</div>
				</section>

				<!-- Rate Limits -->
				<section>
					<h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-white mb-4">Rate Limits</h2>
					<p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-4">
						API requests are limited to <strong>1000 requests per hour</strong> per API key.
					</p>
					<p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
						When the rate limit is exceeded, you'll receive a 429 status code with a 
						<code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-900 px-1 rounded">Retry-After</code> header indicating when you can make requests again.
					</p>
				</section>
			</div>
		</div>
	</body>
</html>

